ally to distinguish a son from a father bearing the same given name, or a local name from Fitz in Shropshire, named with the Old English personal name <i>Fitt</i> + <i>hōh</i> ‘hill spur’."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":36,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705188,"age":45,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"When Bertram Fitz Haute was born in 1179, in France, his father, Piers de Lorraine Fitz Haute, was 113 and his mother, Mrs. Piers Fitz Haute, was 110. He had at least 1 son with Mrs. Bertram Fitz Haute. He died in 1249, in England, at the age of 70."},"et":{"1179–1249":"1179–1249","1117–1185":"1117–1185","1179–Female":"1179–Surnud","1203–1250":"1203–1250","1066–1139":"1066–1139","1069–Female":"1069–Surnud","1249":"1249","1139":"1139","1117":"1117","1215":"1215","1203":"1203","1224":"1224","1179":"1179","1069":"1069","1066":"1066","1185":"1185","1250":"1250","Waltham, Kent, England":"Waltham, Kent, England","England":"England","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1179–1249":"1179–1249","1117–1185":"1117–1185","1179–Female":"1179–Kuollut","1203–1250":"1203–1250","1066–1139":"1066–1139","1069–Female":"1069–Kuollut","1249":"1249","1139":"1139","1117":"1117","1215":"1215","1203":"1203","1224":"1224","1179":"1179","1069":"1069","1066":"1066","1185":"1185"